Connector catalog reference data (community tier)
-------------------------------------------------
The connector catalog MAY include community-tier reference rows derived from
provider metadata published by:

    open-connector — https://github.com/oomol-lab/open-connector
    Copyright (c) oomol-lab and contributors
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

These rows are imported as UNTRUSTED reference data by the offline tool in
crates/fluidbox-catalog-import (see
docs/superpowers/plans/2026-07-14-connector-catalog-bulk-import.md). Each such
row records its origin in its `provenance` column
({"source":"open-connector","source_ref":"<pinned commit>", ...}), and the
generated migration header records the exact upstream commit it was produced
from. No open-connector source code is vendored, executed, or linked; only
factual provider metadata (names, descriptions, categories, auth types, and
scopes) is redistributed, with attribution, per the Apache-2.0 license.

The default checked-in catalog ships only fluidbox-curated (verified) rows;
an open-connector import migration is merged separately and is gated on the
attribution/legal review noted in the plan (D7 / open question O1).
